<tool id="ssrfilter" name="Filtering SSR" version="0.1.0" profile="25.0">
    <description>
        for missing data (individuals and loci), and null alleles.
    </description>

    <requirements>
        <requirement type="package" version="4.3.3">r-base</requirement>
        <requirement type="package" version="2.9.8">r-poppr</requirement>
        <requirement type="package" version="2.1.11">r-adegenet</requirement>
        <requirement type="package" version="0.5_11">r-hierfstat</requirement>
    </requirements>

    <required_files>
        <include path="SSR_filtering.R" />
    </required_files>

    <command detect_errors="exit_code"><![CDATA[
        mkdir -p filter_output &&
        mkdir -p summary &&
        mkdir -p figure_output &&

        Rscript '$__tool_directory__/SSR_filtering.R'
            --input '${input_data}'
            --name '${input_data.element_identifier}'
            --order '${filter_order}'
            --ind-md '${filter_ind_md.ind_md}'
            --ssr-md '${filter_ssr_md.ssr_md}'
            --low-quar '${filter_null_allele.low_quar}'
            --high-quar '${filter_null_allele.high_quar}'
            --multi '${filter_null_allele.multi}'

    ]]></command>
    
    <inputs>
        <param name="input_data" type="data" format="tabular,txt" label="Upload your SSR genotype file"
            help="Tabular file with individuals in rows and loci in columns. See format below."/>

        <param name="filter_order" type="select" multiple="true" display="checkboxes"
            label="Select and order the filters to apply"
            help="Only the selected filters will be applied, in the exact order chosen here.">
            <option value="A">A: Individuals with missing data </option>
            <option value="B">B: Loci with missing data</option>
            <option value="C">C: Null alleles (paralogues) </option>
        </param>

    
        <section name="filter_ind_md" title="[A] Individuals with missing data" expanded="false">
            <param name="ind_md" type="float" value="0.30" min="0" max="1"
                label="Maximum of missing data allowed per individual (MAX_MISSING_IND)"/>
        </section>

        <section name="filter_ssr_md" title="[B] Loci with missing data" expanded="false">
            <param name="ssr_md" type="float" value="0.30" min="0" max="1"
                label="Maximum of missing allowed data per locus (MAX_MISSING_LOCI)"/>
        </section>

        <section name="filter_null_allele" title="[C] Null alleles (paralogues)" expanded="false">
            <param name="low_quar" type="float" value="0.25" min="0" max="1"
                label="Lower quartile for IQR method"/>
            <param name="high_quar" type="float" value="0.75" min="0" max="1"
                label="Upper quartile for IQR method"/>
            <param name="multi" type="float" value="1.5" min="0"
                label="IQR multiplier"/>
        </section>
    </inputs>

    <outputs>
        <data name="filtered_data" format="tabular" label="${tool.name}">
            <discover_datasets pattern="(?P&lt;designation&gt;.+)\.txt$" directory="filter_output" visible="true" assign_primary_output="true"/>
        </data>
        
        <data name="filtering_summary" format="tabular" from_work_dir="summary/filtering_summary.txt" label=" Filtering: Number of loci and individuals"/>

        <data name="boxplot_fis" format="png" label="Fis distribution boxplot — null allele filter">
            <discover_datasets pattern="(?P&lt;designation&gt;.+)\.png$" directory="figure_output" visible="true" assign_primary_output="true"/>
            <filter>'C' in filter_order</filter>
        </data>
    </outputs>

    <tests>
        <test expect_num_outputs="2">
            <param name="input_data" value="test_SSR.txt"/>
            <param name="filter_order" value="A"/>
            <section name="filter_ind_md">
                <param name="ind_md" value="0.1"/>
            </section>
            <output name="filtered_data" count="1" ftype="tabular">
                <assert_contents>
                    <has_n_lines n="192"/>
                    <has_n_columns n="48"/>
                    <has_text text="Lobo004"/>
                </assert_contents>
            </output>
            <output name="filtering_summary" ftype="tabular">
                <assert_contents>
                    <has_n_lines n="3"/>
                    <has_n_columns n="6"/>
                    <has_line_matching expression="File\tStep\tFilter\tParams\tn_ind\tn_loci"/>
                    <has_line_matching expression="test_SSR\t1\tIndividuals missing data\tMAX_MISSING_IND=0.1\t191\t46"/>
                </assert_contents>
            </output>
        </test>

        <test expect_num_outputs="2">
            <param name="input_data" value="test_SSR.txt"/>
            <param name="filter_order" value="B"/>
            <section name="filter_ssr_md">
                <param name="ssr_md" value="0.1"/>
            </section>
            <output name="filtered_data" count="1" ftype="tabular">
                <assert_contents>
                    <has_n_lines n="219"/>
                    <has_n_columns n="43"/>
                    <has_text text="Lobo004"/>
                </assert_contents>
            </output>
            <output name="filtering_summary" ftype="tabular">
                <assert_contents>
                    <has_n_lines n="3"/>
                    <has_n_columns n="6"/>
                    <has_line_matching expression="File\tStep\tFilter\tParams\tn_ind\tn_loci"/>
                    <has_line_matching expression="test_SSR\t1\tLoci missing data\tMAX_MISSING_LOCI=0.1\t218\t41"/>
                </assert_contents>
            </output>
        </test>

        <test expect_num_outputs="3">
            <param name="input_data" value="test_SSR.txt"/>
            <param name="filter_order" value="C"/>
            <section name="filter_null_allele">
                <param name="low_quar" value="0.25"/>
                <param name="high_quar" value="0.75"/>
                <param name="multi" value="1.5"/>
            </section>
            <output name="filtered_data" count="1" ftype="tabular">
                <assert_contents>
                    <has_n_lines n="219"/>
                    <has_n_columns n="48"/>
                    <has_text text="Lobo004"/>
                </assert_contents>
            </output>
            <output name="filtering_summary" ftype="tabular">
                <assert_contents>
                    <has_n_lines n="3"/>
                    <has_n_columns n="6"/>
                    <has_line_matching expression="File\tStep\tFilter\tParams\tn_ind\tn_loci"/>
                    <has_line_matching expression="test_SSR\t1\tNull alleles\tlow_quar=0.25, high_quar=0.75, IQR_multi=1.5\t218\t46"/>
                </assert_contents>
            </output>
            <output name="boxplot_fis" ftype="png" count="1">
                <assert_contents>
                    <has_image_height height="600"/>
                </assert_contents>
            </output>
        </test>

        <test expect_num_outputs="3">
            <param name="input_data" value="test_SSR.txt"/>
            <param name="filter_order" value="A,B,C"/>
            <section name="filter_ind_md">
                <param name="ind_md" value="0.1"/>
            </section>
            <section name="filter_ssr_md">
                <param name="ssr_md" value="0.1"/>
            </section>
            <section name="filter_null_allele">
                <param name="low_quar" value="0.25"/>
                <param name="high_quar" value="0.75"/>
                <param name="multi" value="1.5"/>
            </section>
            <output name="filtered_data" count="1" ftype="tabular">
                <assert_contents>
                    <has_n_lines n="192"/>
                    <has_n_columns n="45"/>
                    <has_text text="Lobo004"/>
                </assert_contents>
            </output>
            <output name="filtering_summary" ftype="tabular">
                <assert_contents>
                    <has_n_lines n="5"/>
                    <has_n_columns n="6"/>
                    <has_line_matching expression="File\tStep\tFilter\tParams\tn_ind\tn_loci"/>
                    <has_line_matching expression="test_SSR\t3\tNull alleles\tlow_quar=0.25, high_quar=0.75, IQR_multi=1.5\t191\t43"/>
                </assert_contents>
            </output>
            <output name="boxplot_fis" ftype="png" count="1">
                <assert_contents>
                    <has_image_height height="600"/>
                </assert_contents>
            </output>
        </test>
    </tests>

    <help><![CDATA[
Usage
=====

This tool filters microsatellite (SSR) genotype data by applying up to four filters in a user-defined order. The user selects which filters to apply and the order. Each filter has its own set of parameters accessible in the corresponding section below.

**Available filters:**

1. **Remove individuals with too much missing data** — removes individuals whose proportion of missing genotypes exceeds the defined threshold.
2. **Remove loci with too much missing data** — removes SSR loci whose proportion of missing genotypes across individuals exceeds the defined threshold.
3. **Filter null alleles (paralogues)** — detects loci likely carrying null or paralogous alleles based on the distribution of Fis across loci. Outlier loci are identified using the IQR method: loci whose Fis falls outside ``[Q1 - k*IQR, Q3 + k*IQR]`` are removed. The quartiles (Q1, Q3) and the multiplier (k) are user-defined. When only one population is present, Fis is estimated per locus as ``1 - Ho/He``.

The order of filter application follows the order selected in the filter list.

Input format
============

**SSR genotype file (tab-separated):**

::

    Ind     Pop     Loc1    Loc2    Loc3
    ind1    pop1    120/124 200/202 150/150
    ind2    pop1    120/120 202/204 150/152
    ind3    pop2    124/126 200/200 152/152
    ind4    pop2    NA      200/202 150/152

Missing genotypes should be encoded as ``NA``.

Outputs
=======

- **Filtered SSR dataset** — genotype table after applying all selected filters, in the same format as the input.
- **Filtering log** — step-by-step log detailing which individuals or loci were removed at each filter step.
- **Filtering summary report** — tabular summary of the number of individuals and loci before and after each filter step, with retention rates.

    ]]></help>

